 791:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** /*******************************************************************************
 792:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * Function Name: Bootloader_Start
 793:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** ****************************************************************************//**
 794:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * \brief
 795:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *  This function is called to execute the following algorithm:
 796:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *
 797:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * -    Validate the Bootloadable application for the Classic Single-app Bootloader or 
 798:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *   both Bootloadable/Combination applications for the Classic Dual-app Bootloader/
 799:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *   Launch-only Bootloader (Launcher for short) respectively.
 800:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *  
 801:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * -    For the Classic Single-app Bootloader: if the Bootloadable application is valid, 
 802:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *   then the flow switches to it after a software reset. Otherwise it stays in 
 803:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *   the Bootloader, waiting for a command(s) from the host.
 804:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * 
 805:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * -    For the Classic Dual-app Bootloader: the flow acts according to the switching table 
 806:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *  (see in the code below) and enabled/disabled options (for instance, auto-switching).
 807:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *   NOTE If the valid Bootloadable application is identified, then the control is passed 
 808:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *   to it after a software reset. Otherwise it stays in the Classic Dual-app Bootloader 
 809:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *   waiting for a command(s) from the host.
 810:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * 
 811:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * -    For the Launcher: the flow acts according to the switching table (see below) and 
 812:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *   enabled/disabled options. NOTE If the valid Combination application is identified, then 
 813:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *   the control is passed to it after a software reset. Otherwise it stays in the Launcher 
 814:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *   forever.
 815:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * 
 816:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * -    Validate the Bootloader/Launcher application(s) (design-time configurable, Bootloader 
 817:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *   application validation option of the component customizer).
 818:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * 
 819:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * -    Run a communication subroutine (design-time configurable, the Wait for command 
 820:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *   option of the component customizer). NOTE This is NOT applicable for the Launcher.
 821:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *
 822:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * -    Schedule the Bootloadable and reset the device.
 823:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *
 824:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *  \ref page_switching_logic
 825:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *
 826:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** * \return
 827:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *  This method will never return. It will either load a new application and
 828:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *  reset the device or jump directly to the existing application. The CPU is
 829:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *  halted, if the validation fails when the "Bootloader application validation" 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\theGu\AppData\Local\Temp\ccgxDzgd.s 			page 16


 830:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *  option is enabled.
 831:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *  PSoC 3/PSoC 5: The CPU is halted if flash initialization fails.
 832:Generated_Source\PSoC4/Bootloader.c **** *
